# Curve448 RFC 7748 §5.2 / §6.2 KAT Spec
#
# Exercises os.crypto.curve448.x448_scalar_mult and x448_dh against the
# canonical RFC 7748 reference values.
#
# Vectors covered:
#   TV1    — RFC 7748 §5.2 X448 test vector 1
#   TV2    — RFC 7748 §5.2 X448 test vector 2
#   ITER1  — RFC 7748 §5.2 X448 after 1 iteration (base_point × 5 starting value)
#   ECDH   — RFC 7748 §6.2 Alice + Bob DH exchange
#
# The 1000-iteration and 1000000-iteration checks from RFC 7748 §5.2 are
# omitted: 1000 iterations exceeds the 60s per-it interpreter watchdog
# (same perf cliff as ed448 — see doc/02_requirements/feature/
# ed448_dedicated_field_arithmetic_2026-05-02.md).
# Filed as perf FR: doc/02_requirements/feature/x448_iteration_kat_perf_fr.md
#
# All byte values verified via Python cryptography library against the
# plain-text RFC 7748 (rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc7748.txt).
#
# Function signatures (os.crypto.curve448):
#   x448_scalar_mult(scalar: [u8], u_coord: [u8]) -> [u8]  # 56-byte output
#   x448_keygen(seed: [u8]) -> [list]                       # [priv, pub]
#   x448_dh(priv: [u8], peer_pub: [u8]) -> [u8]
#   x448_clamp(scalar: [u8]) -> [u8]

use std.spipe.*
use os.crypto.curve448.{x448_scalar_mult, x448_keygen, x448_dh, x448_clamp}

